92275810-d6be-4c3f-a368-4a41d7cfe812.text:
For purposes of these requirements there are two entities that interact with a general-purpose computing 
platform: &lt;ol type="1"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Users (unprivileged users)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Administrators (privileged users)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;
Users are humans who interact with the platform through user interfaces. They usually have to authenticate 
themselves to tenant software (e.g. an operating system), but generally not to the platform itself. Throughout
this document the term "user" refers generally to a person interacting with the platform.&lt;p/&gt;
Administrators are users who manage the platform through a management interface. The interface
may be local or remote to the platform. &lt;p/&gt;
Administrators manage the physical platform, not the OS (OS Administrators would be classified
as platform Users). Administrators must be authenticated to the platform before the platform can allow them 
to perform administrative functions. For an EUD, this could be accomplished through an interface implemented 
in firmware. For server-class hardware, the management interface could be implemented in a management
controller that is part of the platform. Administrators are assumed to be acting in the best interests of the platform owner.&lt;p/&gt;
Tenant Software generally consists of an operating system, virtualization system, or application
that uses platform resources to run workloads on behalf of Users. Tenant software generally has the privilege 
of the User or Administrator in whose context it runs.&lt;p/&gt;

036f8a28-38e9-45a9-b10c-20dd5eeffa75.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
						The TSF shall derive shared cryptographic keys with input from multiple parties in accordance with specified cryptographic key agreement algorithms &lt;assignable&gt;cryptographic algorithm&lt;/assignable&gt; and specified cryptographic parameters &lt;assignable&gt;cryptographic parameters&lt;/assignable&gt; that meet the following: &lt;assignable&gt;list of standards&lt;/assignable&gt;.
					&lt;/title&gt;

61eccacb-3aee-4008-a906-afd82da9b45e.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
			The TSF shall implement the IPsec protocol ESP as defined by RFC 4303 using the cryptographic 
			algorithms &lt;assignable&gt;cryptographic algorithms&lt;/assignable&gt;
			together with a Secure Hash Algorithm (SHA)-based HMAC.
                &lt;/title&gt;

faaee711-0ddd-48a1-a5e4-b313f772940e.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
			The TSF shall ensure the encrypted payload in the &lt;assignable&gt;key exchange protocol&lt;/assignable&gt;
                   protocol uses the cryptographic algorithms &lt;assignable&gt;cryptographic algorithms&lt;/assignable&gt; and no other algorithm.
                &lt;/title&gt;

3f41122d-fb26-4481-8af0-ca5561a6285f.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
			    The TSF shall ensure that all IKE protocols implement DH groups &lt;assignable&gt;DH Groups&lt;/assignable&gt;.
			    &lt;/title&gt;

72c6a69c-cb71-4201-b647-3105a02a7b8f.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;The TSF shall ensure that all IKE protocols perform peer authentication using a
			&lt;assignable&gt;IKE peer authentication algorithm&lt;/assignable&gt;
			that use X.509v3 certificates that conform to RFC 4945 and 
			&lt;assignable&gt;other IKE peer authentication mechanism&lt;/assignable&gt;.
			&lt;/title&gt;

8a60bcf6-a04a-44da-83e5-6e336ee79e6f.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;The TSF shall not establish an SA if the &lt;assignable&gt;specific certificate reference identifier&lt;/assignable&gt;
			and &lt;assignable&gt;other certificate reference identifier type&lt;/assignable&gt; contained in a certificate does
			not match the expected value(s) for the entity attempting to establish a connection.
		&lt;/title&gt;

02c07d79-ad82-4757-8bbe-94339437da0f.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall provide &lt;assignable&gt;protected storage type&lt;/assignable&gt;
					protected storage for asymmetric private keys and 
					&lt;assignable&gt;secrets to be stored&lt;/assignable&gt;.
				&lt;/title&gt;

897246e5-6a4e-4170-b008-dc310250cd66.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall support the capability of 
					&lt;assignable&gt;capability for acquiring keys&lt;/assignable&gt;
					upon request of &lt;assignable&gt;entity requesting storage&lt;/assignable&gt;. 
				&lt;/title&gt;

2a573cf0-0545-4e78-9ee4-51a7a2109070.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall be capable of destroying keys/secrets in the protected storage
					upon request of &lt;assignable&gt;authorized subject&lt;/assignable&gt;.&lt;/title&gt;

9aea26ba-452f-4321-a464-90939a37a6f2.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall encrypt &lt;assignable&gt;types of key material&lt;/assignable&gt; using 
					&lt;assignable&gt;cryptographic algorithm&lt;/assignable&gt;.
					&lt;/title&gt;

ee38e5de-46fe-4c71-86c0-f8c0cf641260.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall protect the integrity of any encrypted 
					&lt;assignable&gt;types of key material&lt;/assignable&gt; by using 
					&lt;assignable&gt;integrity protection mechanism&lt;/assignable&gt;.
				&lt;/title&gt;

1a9b99d0-0f81-4447-9bb5-c1582feb60f5.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall support importing keys/key material using 
					&lt;assignable&gt;import mechanism&lt;/assignable&gt;.
				&lt;/title&gt;

5e15d7c1-72bf-4720-8f7b-ea1158c9fada.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall verify the integrity of imported keys/key material using 
					&lt;assignable&gt;integrity verification method&lt;/assignable&gt;.
				&lt;/title&gt;

842f6b66-90c3-4058-8e10-dc6b9c0125d0.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall implement a trusted execution environment that conforms to the following
					standard: &lt;assignable&gt;Trusted Execution Environment standard&lt;/assignable&gt; 
					and make this TEE available to tenant software.&lt;/title&gt;

a652dbd4-f853-4936-bf85-7a35e4cc1688.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
						The TSF shall consider password and 
						&lt;assignable&gt;other authentication mechanisms&lt;/assignable&gt;
						as critical authentication mechanisms.
					&lt;/title&gt;

4a755521-da1c-4db1-b22f-01a4c8d47c56.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;The integrity of platform firmware shall be rooted in 
					&lt;assignable&gt;platform firmware root of trust&lt;/assignable&gt;.
				&lt;/title&gt;

ec9dd659-7acf-4d7f-bafb-59c8bef2525f.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TOE shall take the following actions if an integrity check specified in FPT_ROT_EXT.3.1 fails:
					&lt;ol type="1"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Halt,&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Notify an 
							&lt;selectables&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;Administrator&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;User&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;/selectables&gt; by &lt;assignable&gt;notification method&lt;/assignable&gt;, and&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;selectables linebreak="yes" onlyone="yes"&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;Stop all execution and shut down&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;Continue execution without the integrity-compromised component&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;Continue execution&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;/selectables&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;selectables linebreak="yes" onlyone="yes"&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;in accordance with administrator-configurable policy&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;by express determination of an 
							&lt;selectables&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;Administrator&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;User&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;/selectables&gt;&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;/selectables&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;.	
				&lt;/title&gt;

ae59c886-d7bc-44e5-86a4-df2fd736f172.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall implement a mechanism for recovering from boot firmware failure consisting of 
					&lt;assignable&gt;recovery mechanism&lt;/assignable&gt;.
				&lt;/title&gt;

4540e4bc-b2d0-4297-85e9-2782f0848f4a.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall allow installation of updates only if the digital signature has been
					successfully verified as specified in FCS_COP.1 and 
					&lt;assignable&gt;additional constraints on updates&lt;/assignable&gt;.
				&lt;/title&gt;

654ddfa5-7c4e-4546-95d9-c791ad0cb422.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TOE shall take the following actions if a platform firmware integrity, authenticity, 
					or rollback-prevention check fails, or a platform firmware update fails for any other reason: 
					&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Do not install the update,&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generate an audit event (optional),&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;and
					&lt;selectables linebreak="yes" onlyone="yes"&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;Continue execution&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;Halt&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;Stop all execution and shut down&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;Initiate recovery as specified in FPT_RVR_EXT.1&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;/selectables&gt;&lt;selectables linebreak="yes" onlyone="yes"&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;automatically&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;in accordance with Administrator-configurable policy&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;by express determination of a User&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;/selectables&gt;.
				&lt;/title&gt;

cbc5790e-2cdf-48ab-be4f-58cba140f8ae.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall allow execution or use of platform firmware updates only if new platform firmware
					is integrity- and authenticity-checked using the mechanism described in FPT_ROT_EXT.2 prior to its
					execution or use, and &lt;assignable&gt;additional constraints on update&lt;/assignable&gt;.
				&lt;/title&gt;

8739dbd9-9642-4df0-96d1-76d9b0c804d1.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TOE shall take the following actions if a platform firmware update integrity, authentication, or
					rollback-prevention check fails, or a platform firmware update fails for any other reason:
					&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Do not install the update,&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Generate an audit event (optional),&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;and
					&lt;selectables linebreak="yes" onlyone="yes"&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;Continue execution&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;Halt&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;Stop all execution and shut down&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable id="sel-tud3-recovery"&gt;Initiate recovery as specified in FPT_RVR_EXT.1&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;/selectables&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;selectables linebreak="yes" onlyone="yes"&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;automatically&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable id="sel-tud3-admin-config"&gt;in accordance with administrator-configurable policy&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;selectable&gt;by express determination of a User&lt;/selectable&gt;&lt;/selectables&gt;.
				&lt;/title&gt;

e6589832-6a09-4378-bb9e-b12861e88fb8.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					A user shall assert physical presence to the TSF through: 
					&lt;assignable&gt;method for asserting physical presence&lt;/assignable&gt;.
				&lt;/title&gt;

13832fbd-91c4-4f15-901e-452cf0f74990.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall use &lt;assignable&gt;trusted channel protocols&lt;/assignable&gt;
					protocols with &lt;assignable&gt;authentication mechanism&lt;/assignable&gt;
					to provide a communication channel between itself and 
					&lt;assignable&gt;external IT entities&lt;/assignable&gt;
					that is logically distinct from other communication channels, provides assured 
					identification of its end points, protects channel data from disclosure, and detects modification
					of the channel data. 
				&lt;/title&gt;

fff59065-fe96-48d9-858f-23cf9f910d05.extCompDefTitle:
&lt;title&gt;
					The TSF shall encrypt data for transfer between the TOE and 
					&lt;assignable&gt;list of entities external to the TOE&lt;/assignable&gt;
					using a cryptographic algorithm and key size as specified in
					FCS_COP.1, and using &lt;assignable&gt;key establishment mechanism&lt;/assignable&gt;.
				&lt;/title&gt;
